cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT

This paper deals with the analysis and defense of encounter-based networks, which are wireless ad-hoc networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the propagation of worms and their interaction with the network, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The mathematical modeling and analysis of worm interactions involve the use of differential equations, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the impact of network and node characteristics on worm propagation, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of protocols to counter worm attacks, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
